cately-decorated-coffin-and-rare-treasures-from-his-reign-at-this-new-immersive-exhibition-180988306/</guid></item><item><title>观看 2,500 磅重的青铜野牛抵达史密森尼国家自然历史博物馆的新永久地点</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-2500-pound-bronze-bison-as-they-arrive-at-their-new-permanent-place-at-the-smithsonians-national-museum-of-natural-history-180988387/</link><description>一个多世纪前，这种大型哺乳动物实际上在史密森尼城堡旁边吃草。截至今天，博物馆主入口两侧的两座大型雕塑延续了这一传统</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 17:12:47 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/see-the-2500-pound-bronze-bison-as-they-arrive-at-their-new-permanent-place-at-the-smithsonians-national-museum-of-natural-history-180988387/</guid></item><item><title>在印加帝国崛起之前，人类可能已经沿着复杂的贸易路线将活鹦鹉运过安第斯山脉</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humans-may-have-transported-live-parrots-over-the-andes-mountains-along-sophisticated-trade-routes-before-the-rise-of-the-inca-empire-180988377/</link><description>当考古学家在秘鲁沿海的印加前墓葬中发现鹦鹉羽毛时，他们感到很困惑。一项新的研究表明，这些鸟是在野外捕获的，并在漫长的旅程中保持活力</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 16:20:44 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/humans-may-have-transported-live-parrots-over-the-andes-mountains-along-sophisticated-trade-routes-before-the-rise-of-the-inca-empire-180988377/</guid></item><item><title>科学家在解决令人毛骨悚然的静电之谜方面取得重大突破</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-make-a-major-breakthrough-in-solving-a-hair-raising-mystery-about-static-electricity-180988382/</link><description>这些发现有助于解释火山闪电等现象背后的物理原理</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 15:29:38 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/scientists-make-a-major-breakthrough-in-solving-a-hair-raising-mystery-about-static-electricity-180988382/</guid></item><item><title>欧洲刺猬的听力可能会适应超声波。这一发现可以帮助科学家拯救正在衰落的物种</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/european-hedgehogs-hearing-might-be-attuned-to-ultrasonic-sounds-the-discovery-could-help-scientists-save-the-declining-species-180988383/</link><description>基于声音的威慑可以帮助动物远离快速行驶的汽车和危险的景观设备</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 14:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/european-hedgehogs-hearing-might-be-attuned-to-ultrasonic-sounds-the-discovery-could-help-scientists-save-the-declining-species-180988383/</guid></item><item><title>在罗马斗兽场，新的大理石板标志着数千年前矗立的高耸柱子的位置</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/at-the-colosseum-new-marble-slabs-mark-where-towering-columns-stood-thousands-of-years-ago-180988378/</link><description>人群曾经聚集在两个由 164 英尺高的柱子支撑的高拱廊下面。但由于地震和地基不稳定，这些建筑元素早已倒塌</description><pubDate>Fri, 20 Mar 2026 11:00:00 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/at-the-colosseum-new-marble-slabs-mark-where-towering-columns-stood-thousands-of-years-ago-180988378/</guid></item><item><title>英格兰的“康斯特布尔之国”将举办为期一年的展览，庆祝其同名景观艺术家约翰·康斯特布尔 (John Constable) 诞辰 250 周年</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/englands-constable-country-is-honoring-the-250th-birthday-of-its-namesake-landscape-artist-john-constable-with-a-year-of-exhibitions-180988381/</link><description>康斯特布尔于 1776 年 6 月 11 日出生于萨福克郡的东伯格霍特村。附近的伊普斯威奇以“康斯特布尔 250”来纪念这位田园画家与其祖国、社区、国家和当代艺术的联系</description><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 19:44:39 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/englands-constable-country-is-honoring-the-250th-birthday-of-its-namesake-landscape-artist-john-constable-with-a-year-of-exhibitions-180988381/</guid></item><item><title>一名场地管理员注意到高尔夫球场上有一个污水坑。原来是一个装满空瓶的酒窖，100多年来未曾动过</title><link>https://www.smithsonianmag.com/smart-news/a-groundskeeper-noticed-a-sinkhole-on-a-golf-course-it-turned-out-to-be-a-wine-cellar-full-of-empty-bottles-untouched-for-more-than-100-years-180988379/</link><description>该酒窖位于英格兰达维休姆公园高尔夫俱乐部球场的第 13 洞附近。工作人员认为它以前是一座庄园的一​​部分，于 1888 年被拆除</description><pubDate>Thu, 19 Mar 2026 19:04:53 GMT